Introduction

Eunha is a South Korean singer under Big Planet Made. She is a member of the girl group VIVIZ and a member of the girl group GFRIEND. She also used to be part of the project girl group Sunny Girls. Eunha trained at Big Hit Entertainment along with SinB for 1 year.

She debuted as a member of GFriend with the EP Season of Glass on January 15, 2015.

GFriend disbanded on May 22, 2021, after all members left Source Music upon the completion of their six-year contract.

On October 6, 2021, it was announced that Eunha, along with former GFriend members, SinB and Umji, signed a contract with BPM Entertainment to debut as a three-member group. On October 8, 2021, it was announced their new group name would be VIVIZ. VIVIZ debuted on February 9, 2022, with the mini album Beam of Prism.
